So what exactly do you think is awkward about Go's way of working with JSON? Here's a code example from one of my current projects:<p><pre><code>    type UploadProgress struct {
        Progress int `json:"progress"`
    }

    //...
    // variable progress is of type Progress
    if json_data, err := json.Marshal(progress); err == nil {
        w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
        w.Write(json_data)
    }
</code></pre>
json.Unmarshal works the same way. IMHO, not exactly more awkward than using JSON.parse and JSON.stringify.
